                  This is the first accordion item. Each <span class="text-danger">accordion</span>
                  contains <span class="text-danger">accordion-item</span>. accordion-item contains
                  <span class="text-danger">accordion-header</span> and <span class="text-danger">accordion-body</span>.
                  accordion-header contains <span class="text-danger">accordion-button</span>.
                  accordion-item can be opened by adding <span class="text-danger">open</span>
                  class to it. <span class="text-danger">no-collapse</span> class will prevent
                  accordion-item from opening. Add <span class="text-danger">parent</span>
                  attribute to
                  each accordion-item so that only one accordion-item is opened at a time. If you omit the
                  parent attribute the accordion-item will always remain opened. Add <span
                     class="text-danger">no-arrow</span> class to accordion-item to hide the arrow.
               </p>
            </div>
         </div>
